[I] Makes power profiles handling available over D-Bus

[T] power-profiles-daemon offers to modify system behavior based upon
[T] user-selected power profiles.
[T]
[T] There are 3 different power profiles, a "balanced" default mode,
[T] a "power-saver" mode, as well as a "performance" mode. The first 2 of those
[T] are available on every system. The "performance" mode is only available on
[T] select systems and is implemented by different "drivers" based on
[T] the system or systems it targets.

[U] https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/upower/power-profiles-daemon

[A] Red Hat, Inc.
[M] Tomas Glozar <tglozar@gmail.com>

[C] extra/tool
[F] CROSS

